The paper deals with communication complexity, which is a topic in theoretical computer science and falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) as it studies the amount of communication required to solve a problem. The problems studied, inner product and set disjointness, are fundamental problems in computer science and are related to data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper involves some geometric arguments, which could place it under computational geometry (cs.CG).
